    <text>
        <body><div type="bibliography">
                
                <p><bibl><ptr target="#gasperini1967a"/>, p. 166, n. <citedRange>4</citedRange> (dr.) 
                    (= <bibl><ptr target="#gasperini2008"/>, p. <citedRange>77</citedRange></bibl>)</bibl>;
                    <bibl><ptr target="#IGCyr"/> <citedRange>000410</citedRange></bibl>.</p>
            
            </div><div type="edition" xml:lang="grc" xml:space="preserve">
                
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>φ<unclear>α</unclear></orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/>
	 </ab>
            </div><div type="apparatus" xml:space="preserve">
            
                <p><app loc="1"><rdg resp="#gasperini1967a"><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>φ<unclear>α</unclear></orig><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/></rdg>
                     <rdg resp="#gasperini1967a"><lb rend="right-to-left"/><gap reason="lost" extent="unknown" unit="character"/><orig>φ<unclear>δ</unclear></orig></rdg>
                    <note resp="cdl">it might also be read <orig>φ<unclear>λ</unclear></orig></note>
                </app></p>
 </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="fr">
            <p>Intraduisible.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="en">
            <p>Not usefully translatable.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="it">
            <p>Intraducibile.</p>
         </div><div type="translation" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="ar">
            <p>غير قابل للترجمه بشكل جيد</p>
         </div><div type="commentary">
                
                <p>Gasperini's indication about the direction of writing are somewhat confusing. Both readings proposed by him should be read from left to right.
                Moreover there seems no need to admit a delta with the shape of a Latin D for the second character.</p>
                <p>All suggested readings being meaningless, neither seems compulsory, but for the fact that no Greek word would admit a group <foreign xml:lang="grc">ΦΔ</foreign>.</p>
	<p/>
            </div></body>
    </text>
